0-5ad35ce35404" class="r-1i69y5a" loading="eager"/></picture><picture data-rid="039df64a-7dfa-44fe-aa4f-86619163d592" class="r-8t1rys"><img src="https://images.replocdn.com/images/e9c38b45-365a-49ae-87d0-5160b2c9afec/f1a70b15-9943-4e7a-9fc7-bce447bc08da" class="r-h66l5t" loading="eager"/></picture><picture data-rid="203901de-dc25-4727-b50b-3cedc2d131f1" class="r-1rk41mh"><img src="https://images.replocdn.com/images/e9c38b45-365a-49ae-87d0-5160b2c9afec/0b29a53a-766c-49b9-ae93-9042d8b01dd5" class="r-lr8lqe" loading="eager"/></picture></div></div></div></div><picture data-rid="5b4317e2-6c5a-468e-ae0b-1e75863bdc52" class="r-1chfewx"><img src="https://images.replocdn.com/images/e9c38b45-365a-49ae-87d0-5160b2c9afec/0887e1c2-b77f-4f0f-a822-03649d88f877" class="r-11ltvaw" loading="eager"/></picture></div></div><div data-rid="84a3d462-9bc8-4af1-8a4d-707a4454cad8" class="r-1ms4p2j"><div data-rid="8866ccd8-bc83-433f-84b3-a420913719c3" class="r-b12ms8"><div data-rid="14ba55ed-1ded-44a0-a177-873ddbf34b30" class="r-1qjqv2e"><div data-rid="ecd3d756-a06b-46dc-ba8b-51502e0d36f4" class="r-i1lndy alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>5 Reasons Every Baby Chick Owner Should Add Daily Water Support.</p><p>(Most Owners Miss #4)</p></span></div><div data-rid="9b6b2415-b559-4529-bfb4-cad6de7c490a" class="r-1c73tyn alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p><strong>These common stressors quietly take their toll long before most owners realize what’s happening.</strong></p></span></div></div><div data-rid="0556a1e6-7895-4122-b016-9cff2dec1ab5" class="r-9zm520"><picture data-rid="b2fbdb4a-82fd-48a6-b60f-429860c7f6af" class="r-1208mxs"><source srcSet="https://assets.replocdn.com/projects/fdd5614c-e48f-4183-abe2-06ecde4315b2/7799fcb4-ce14-4725-85ce-ba965cac3105?width=820" media="(max-width: 640px)"/><source srcSet="https://assets.replocdn.com/projects/fdd5614c-e48f-4183-abe2-06ecde4315b2/7799fcb4-ce14-4725-85ce-ba965cac3105?width=1024" media="(min-width: 641px) and (max-width: 1024px)"/><source srcSet="https://assets.replocdn.com/projects/fdd5614c-e48f-4183-abe2-06ecde4315b2/7799fcb4-ce14-4725-85ce-ba965cac3105?width=1800" media="(min-width: 1025px) and (max-width: 2400px)"/><img src="https://assets.replocdn.com/projects/fdd5614c-e48f-4183-abe2-06ecde4315b2/7799fcb4-ce14-4725-85ce-ba965cac3105" class="r-1tyrasc" loading="eager"/></picture><div data-rid="eb3dbe5d-a61b-46e8-8e51-ecb8609633f1" class="r-18x2fv0"><div data-rid="7359785c-cac9-4147-899f-7d3ae1a43f6f" class="r-12pa0bz alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><h3>1. Baby Chicks Dehydrate Faster Than You Think.</h3></span></div><div data-rid="e1e7533a-c1cc-4586-b834-c1b65ef706d5" class="r-lm5awk alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>Chicks lose water faster than adult hens. Heat lamps, warm weather, shipping, and moving to a new home can all affect how much water they keep in their bodies. If chicks do not stay properly hydrated, they may seem tired or weak. Adding daily hydration support to their water helps maintain normal energy levels and keeps them active and alert.</p></span></div></div></div><div data-rid="929013bc-78df-4005-8c1e-97ef808bd4e8" class="r-18wf59a"><div data-rid="bb51bbf1-ac30-4f58-af85-6a103f07d30a" class="r-zwpd27"><div data-rid="5a47c4a7-f473-4a81-afad-2fc9a0b46553" class="r-rwk2c1 alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>2. Their Digestive System Is Still Growing.</p></span></div><div data-rid="a4ffe23e-c4c2-4340-a00c-edddca4acccb" class="r-1jryhoz alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>A baby chick’s digestive system is still developing in the first few weeks. If feed is not broken down properly, chicks may not absorb all the nutrients they need to grow. Supporting healthy gut bacteria helps maintain normal digestion and nutrient absorption. When digestion works well, chicks are better able to grow strong feathers and healthy bodies.</p></span></div><div data-rid="18950537-19db-4688-b4c5-36a1742932a6" class="r-8zlngd alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><br></span></div><div data-rid="c07fc064-f7c3-47f7-a236-95cfcb1d9daf" class="r-21xwsl"><picture data-rid="b85ea80f-c5cd-4cd1-bfcd-6b08ec32d257" class="r-dume56"><source srcSet="https://assets.replocdn.com/projects/fdd5614c-e48f-4183-abe2-06ecde4315b2/db04ee6e-b3f0-4284-9a3d-d2f6ac435cb0?width=120" media="(max-width: 640px)"/><source srcSet="https://assets.replocdn.com/projects/fdd5614c-e48f-4183-abe2-06ecde4315b2/db04ee6e-b3f0-4284-9a3d-d2f6ac435cb0?width=180" media="(min-width: 641px) and (max-width: 1024px)"/><source srcSet="https://assets.replocdn.com/projects/fdd5614c-e48f-4183-abe2-06ecde4315b2/db04ee6e-b3f0-4284-9a3d-d2f6ac435cb0?width=180" media="(min-width: 1025px) and (max-width: 2400px)"/><img src="https://assets.replocdn.com/projects/fdd5614c-e48f-4183-abe2-06ecde4315b2/db04ee6e-b3f0-4284-9a3d-d2f6ac435cb0" class="r-dy6ad3" loading="eager"/></picture><div data-rid="fe169a36-0cd3-4664-bf48-8cf4d9b1a824" class="r-ixo92e"><div data-rid="23f51390-2365-49c1-9b14-c1b3be7a8809" class="r-1rau978"><div data-rid="d61d84ba-ff53-4cfb-b061-784dca45e2d4" class="r-1cko0z9"><picture data-rid="60378e52-47bc-4834-99a8-af492f5959c5" class="r-1oyj2ga"><img src="https://images.replocdn.com/images/e9c38b45-365a-49ae-87d0-5160b2c9afec/be004c47-2b6b-4e49-988c-6639247a86a4" class="r-1kmqir" loading="eager"/></picture></div></div><div data-rid="4e0c8c8f-94e2-4511-90e8-56e3391492c6" class="r-zagody alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>“Watching my flock weaken was terrifying. Hen Harmony is how I make sure they’re strong enough to handle whatever comes next.”</p></span></div><div data-rid="2daf2987-e8aa-4e5f-b0a9-8ec3a057aa36" class="r-89g9gd"><div data-rid="32243f09-7145-4b2f-9f16-fa50b8b8751c" class="r-7jcnqi alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>Michael L.</p></span></div><div data-rid="42821cd1-87b7-41f2-8e79-a38cba68d73b" class="r-x32vjg"><picture data-rid="abfd9034-456b-4da9-aa87-8c2ac0b5946d" class="r-1kfhvbk"><img src="https://images.replocdn.com/images/e9c38b45-365a-49ae-87d0-5160b